    "Name": "Bellerophon",
    "Details": "<color=#F79B26>The Bellerophon was a failed prototype intended to complement the Mackie with its higher speed, but its weapon arrangement made it too unstable.</color>\n\nThis reimagined version of the Bellerophon, developed by the Word of Blake to rectify the shortcomings of the original design, features an endo steel chassis, higher-quality armor, and an Anti-Missile System to keep the 'Mech from becoming too unstable from incoming missile fire. The two Large Lasers have been replaced with a pair of Kinslaughter H-Class ER PPCs, cooled by thirteen double heat sinks, significantly enhancing the 'Mech's performance. Additionally, the SRM-4 missile launcher has been swapped for an LRM-15 launcher, further augmenting its long-range offensive capabilities. Its inherent balance issues, however, remain unaddressed.",
